The number of slices you will need $\blue{y}$ is *proportional* to the number of sandwiches you want to make $\red{x}$. We can think of $\blue{y}$ as a function of $\red{x}$. The equation of this function is

 $\begin{align}
\quad \blue{y} 
 &= \purple{m}\cdot\red{x} \\[1mm]
 &= \purple{2}\cdot\red{x} 
\end{align}$

The constant of proportionality is $\purple{m=2}$ since it takes two slices of bread to make one sandwich.

